# Secrets and credentials
# Nothing in this repo should ever contain real credentials.
# Use Windows Credential Manager (preferred) or environment variables.

# GitHub PAT (for the OpenClaw `manager` helper, not committed here)
# Google app password (Jimothy's Gmail)
# OpenAI API key (for GPT-4o calls on the student's handwriting)

# KVdb bucket ids are *public* (anyone with the URL can read or write
# to a KVdb bucket). Commit them so the bucket id is reproducible
# across machines and survives re-indexing.

# Question papers and mark schemes (PDFs).
# Copyright belongs to the awarding bodies (AQA, Pearson Edexcel, OCR,
# eduqas, WJEC). The PDFs are kept in the local working tree and on
# your machines (so index_papers.py and extract_questions.py can read
# them), but they do not ship with the repo. Re-seed from the local
# gcs-papers share on a fresh clone.
papers/*.pdf

# Local-only paths and per-paper extracted text
papers/*/extracted.txt

# Per-paper raw text dumps from index_papers.py. Rebuildable from
# the original PDFs in this same folder, so don't bloat the repo.
papers/*/raw/

# Per-batch photo transcripts (rebuildable from intake/photos)
transcripts/

# Intake folder: phone photos of the student's handwritten answers and
# the per-page OCR transcripts produced from them. NEVER committed —
# the photos are AQA/Edexcel-copyrighted answer scripts belonging to
# the student, and the OCR transcripts quote the student's writing
# verbatim (spelling mistakes and all). Both belong on this machine
# only, not in the public repo.
intake/
intake/**

# Generated assessment output (rebuildable)
assessments/

# Generated HTML for Pages (rebuildable)
pages/assessments/

# Email outbox (rebuildable)
outbox/

# Private configuration: the student's full name, email, salutation,
# and any other personal data the scripts need. The public repo only
# ever sees a placeholder; the real values live here, gitignored.
# Created on first run; not present until then.
private/

# Standard Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.env
.venv/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Intentionally NOT ignored: index/papers.json, calibration/*.md, src/,
# prompts/. The KVdb bucket ids in papers/*/kvdb-bucket.txt are also
# committed (the bucket is anonymous-PUT; see SETUP.md §3 for the
# "treat as untrusted" rule).
